title: Volleyball roundup: Blue Devils sweep past Bulldogs
text: Volleyball roundup: Blue Devils sweep past Bulldogs Comment Sault Ste. Marie Evening News - Sault Ste. Marie, MI By Staff reports Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:50 AM By Staff reports Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:50 AM SAULTSTE. MARIE â€” Sault High defeated Rudyard 25-11, 25-21, 25-23 in a Straits Area Conference volleyball match Tuesday night. Cece Werner hit 14 kills and had six blocks and six digs for the Blue Devils. Brenna James turned in 12 digs, while Maddi Misiak had five kills and six digs. Jordan Menard added four kills and five digs, while Kelsie Sibbald had three kills and two blocks, Val Gage added three kills, and Jacki Sanderson had 31 assists. The Sault beat Rudyard 25-19, 25-20, 13-15 in the JV match. Ashtyn Bell contributed eight kills, Katja Wilhelms had 15 assists eight digs, four aces and three kills, while Maddie Fitzpatrick added four kills and four digs, and Taylor Atkinson had 10 digs, three assists, two kills and two aces. Sault High visits Onaway Monday. Pickford 3, Brimley 1: The Panthers stopped the Bays 20-25, 25-20, 25-12, 25-14 in Eastern UPConference volleyball Tuesday night. Kayla Rambo hit 14 kills, and had six digs and three blocks for the Panthers. Taylor Thurmes added 10 assists, five digs and five aces, while Taylor Opolka had six kills and three blocks. Sophie McConkey added seven digs, four assists and three aces, while Mickayla Fegan had six digs and three aces. DeTour 3, Cedarville 0:The Raiders swept past the Trojans 25-10, 25-16, 25-15 in EUPC volleyball Tuesday night. Kaalin Crawford dished out 18 assists and compiled 16 service points, including seven aces for the Raiders. Mattie Warner added seven service points with three aces, and had four kills. Sarah Bailey added nine service points, seven kills, five aces and three blocks, while Moriah Reed had 10 assists and three kills. Madison Wilkie had 11 kills and four digs, while Hallie Grzesiek had six digs and four kills. DeTour travels to Brimley Thursday. By Staff reports Sault Ste. Marie Evening News - Sault Ste.
